# ==============================================================================
# CLOUDINARY CONFIGURATION - TWO OPTIONS:
# ==============================================================================

# OPTION 1: Single Account (Fallback) - Use environment variables
# Uncomment these if you want to use environment variables for a single account
# CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
# CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
# CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret

# OPTION 2: Multiple Accounts (Recommended) - Use cloudinary_accounts.json
# Edit the cloudinary_accounts.json file instead with all your accounts
# This is the preferred method for multiple accounts

# ==============================================================================
# NOTES:
# ==============================================================================
# - If cloudinary_accounts.json exists and has accounts, it will be used
# - If not, the system falls back to environment variables above
# - For Render.com deployment, you can use either method
# - JSON file method is better for managing multiple accounts
